I've heard of this kind of scheme: usually, the site is registered outside the scope of Russian laws.
People are taking over.
The buyer makes the payment at the ATM.
"He receives a photo and instructions about where the weapon is hidden", explains Dmitry Kislov, secretary of the Right to Gun Association.
Victor Baranets claims that by applying on the site, you can end up unarmed and behind bars.
