It would be interesting to create a flexible product similar to the Kinect, play with the camera curve and see how that could help define locations.
- As I recall, Microsoft, unlike Google, did not present its glasses to the public.
Don't you think that from the point of view of everyday use of augmented reality technologies, glasses are one of the most promising platforms?
- Of course, walking around with a smartphone with your hands up is not practical but here's what I think: the best option would be a "temporary" augmented reality that would allow you from a cloud platform to switch from glasses to a smartphone.
