Wentzler adds: "There is a need for vigilance".
The Commission has also been asked to submit a proposal for a regulation on the protection of the environment.
They argue that it is not enough to rely on international trademark law, but rather that foreigners should "register in China everything that is likely to be protected", as Wentzler says.
