The Washington law, called I-502, takes effect on December 6, leaving a one-year legal loophole, during which the licensing system will still not exist, while marijuana possession will be legal.
Meanwhile, practical questions remain: how to balance the state mandate that guarantees adequate access to legal marijuana and prohibits the establishment of cannabis shops within a 30-km radius around a school, park, playground or day care center.
